The effect of light protocol was investigated based on the rate of hydrogen production, glycerol consumption and hydrogen yield. The rate of hydrogen production was calculated using the molar volume of hydrogen produced (Δn) at the time of interest (t) together with the culture/photobioreactor volume (V), as denoted in Eq. 1. The molar volume of hydrogen was determined at NTP using the analysed composition of the evolved gas, i.e. ~ 92% (± 1.9%) hydrogen and the balance CO2. Glycerol consumption was evaluated using the molar concentration of glycerol in the system at a specific time (nt), and the glycerol concentration initially in the system (no), as shown in Eq. 2.1Rate of H2productionmolm-3h-1=ΔnH2measuredVt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
